        <num>CC 1305</num>
        <heading>1305.  Prescription where possession is separate</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1305.  Prescription where possession is separate.
When one of the heirs has enjoyed the whole or part of the succession separately, or all the coheirs have possessed separately each a portion of the hereditary effects, he or they who have thus separately possessed, can successfully oppose the suit for a partition of the effects of the succession, if their possession has continued thirty years without interruption.</p>
        </content>
